  <history>
    EMUUROM is created with the TIC-80 fantasy console, a game engine with idiosyncratic retro restrictions, like Pico-8.
    
    EMUUROM's demo was the first TIC-80 game on Steam, and it started its life as a jam game for the Fantasy Console jam 3 in early 2018.
    
    The first post-jam demo was released on Itch.io in 2020, and later that year, the demo was a part of the Bundle for Racial Justice and Equality.
    
    A new demo was released on Steam in Fall 2021 for the Steam Next Fest.
    
    I've documented the development process and new demo updates in my Itch.io devlog (link at the bottom).
    
    EMUUROM has been featured in multiple events, including Thinky Direct 2025, Busan Indie Connect, Nordic Game Conference, Pocket Gamer Connects and multiple Cerebral Puzzle Showcases.
  </history>

